            <div type="translation">
            <p>"If anyone dares to bury another with him, he will deposit in the fiscus thrice-two thousand. 
                     So much will he pay down to Portus, but for this wickedness 
                    he will suffer punishment of a grave-violator.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>Elegiac couplets, marked by the interpunct and the division into columns. The depiction
                    show a chest with a basin for bleeding and surgeon's tools that identify the man
                    as a physician. Line 12-13: τεὶσοι for τεὶσει.</p></div>
            
